M|rules|title: Parallel Nested Data Fetching
M|rules|impact: CRITICAL
M|rules|impactDescription: eliminates server-side waterfalls
M|rules|tags: server, rsc, parallel-fetching, promise-chaining
M|rules|When fetching nested data in parallel, chain dependent fetches within each item's promise so a slow item doesn't block the rest.
M|rules|**Incorrect (a single slow item blocks all nested fetches):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const chats = await Promise.all(
M|rules|chatIds.map(id => getChat(id))
M|rules|)
M|rules|const chatAuthors = await Promise.all(
M|rules|chats.map(chat => getUser(chat.author))
M|rules|)
M|rules|```
M|rules|If one `getChat(id)` out of 100 is extremely slow, the authors of the other 99 chats can't start loading even though their data is ready.
M|rules|**Correct (each item chains its own nested fetch):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const chatAuthors = await Promise.all(
M|rules|chatIds.map(id => getChat(id).then(chat => getUser(chat.author)))
M|rules|)
M|rules|```
M|rules|Each item independently chains `getChat` → `getUser`, so a slow chat doesn't block author fetches for the others.